{"key":"post-13796897","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13796897</id>\n<content>Pelleted lime takes months to break down usually.&amp;nbsp; Since the average life of a casing layer is measured in days to weeks, it probably won't do much good.&amp;nbsp; See if it dissolves in water, which I doubt.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;This is why we recommend hydrated lime for casing layers.&amp;nbsp; It is water soluble and begins working immediately, not six to eight weeks later after you've already tossed the tray out.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13796967</next>\n<prev>13796861</prev>\n<first>13747851</first>\n<last>13802482</last>\n<when>1295210528</when>\n<utime>01/16/11 10:42 PM</utime>\n</post>"}